tetra.logic

Class Piece

  • java.lang.Object
    • tetra.logic.Piece

  • public class Piece
extends Object
    The active piece which the player can control. It should be noted, that the active piece is not considered part of the matrix until it locks into place.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      Piece(Tetromino tetromino, Matrix matrix)
      Class constructor which specifies the first tetromino, and the matrix within which this piece will travel.

      • getBlock

        public Block getBlock(int x,
                      int y)
        Returns the block in the specified (x, y) position, or null if the position is empty. The result depends on the current orientation, since the configuration of blocks is different for each orientation. If the x- or y-coordinate is out of range, returns null.
        Parameters:
        x - x-coordinate of the element to return
        y - y-coordinate of the element to return
        Returns:
        the block at the specified position, or null if the position is empty

      • lock

        public void lock()
        Disassembles the piece into independent blocks, and adds them to the matrix. The blocks are added to the current position of the piece. After this the piece will intersect with the matrix and should be respawned. It should be noted that this method does not modify the piece in any way.

      • respawn

        public boolean respawn(Tetromino next)
        Sets the next tetromino, and moves the piece into its initial position.
        Parameters:
        next - next tetromino
        Returns:
        true if, after respawning, intersects with the matrix, false otherwise
